From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0023/N] pauth_bsd_aarch64: pass-through under CHERI to dodge clang ICE

`pauth_strip_pointer` on FreeBSD/aarch64 uses an inline-asm form
that pins its `address` argument to register `x30`:

  register address result __asm__("x30") = ptr;
  asm (XPACLRI : "+r"(result));

Under CHERI/Morello purecap, `address` is a 128-bit `__intcap`
which lives in capability register `c30`, not the 64-bit X register
`x30`. Asking the clang ISel pass to lower a cap-typed value onto
an X register reliably ICEs the backend.

Logical view: PAuth is a software-mitigations feature that hashes
upper address bits with a key; CHERI capabilities already carry
integrity (tag, bounds, otype) via hardware, so stripping the PAuth
signature is meaningless. Return the pointer unchanged under
__CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0023)

--- a/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_aarch64/pauth_bsd_aarch64.inline.hpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_aarch64/pauth_bsd_aarch64.inline.hpp
@@ -38,7 +38,14 @@
 #define XPACLRI "hint #0x7;"

 inline address pauth_strip_pointer(address ptr) {
-#ifdef __APPLE__
+#if defined(__CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__)
+  // CHERI/Morello purecap: capabilities are not PAuth-signed; the
+  // capability bounds + tag already serve the integrity role. The
+  // pinned-x30 inline-asm form below ICEs Morello clang during ISel
+  // because the cap-typed `address` cannot be lowered onto an X
+  // register. Just return the pointer unchanged.
+  return ptr;
+#elif defined(__APPLE__)
   return ptrauth_strip(ptr, ptrauth_key_asib);
 #else
   register address result __asm__("x30") = ptr;
